spanGrp.span: Fir/if it is a domestic chicken,
Sökö/ se je óshkoro kasero ra
we pluck it, and peal it; its feathers go off,
se je të í kö ye-gẽ rö köye-lë je köyögö jãwẽ-gẽ
sha-bla yís je rö diglö bal nã (m) diglö bal nã (m)
We boil it and have it boiled; then we soak it
and put it on [a table] and throw the feathers away.
patke-gẽ jeska í të í köyögö mĩwẽ-gẽ
and we also cook the feathers with boiling water [???]
jeska sa të í köyögö eliwẽ-gẽ diglö bal wa
Je wa se mi-gẽ í köyö
Köyö-lë je ra bá í köyögö mĩr
We then take out its guts,
Jeska ra se je mĩ-gẽ të ñã' bie-gẽũ-mĩ
cut off its nails and its head.
Then we cut it however we want to eat it.
Jeska í wöbige-gẽ mẽnẽbi sa í kiar kepi mẽnẽbi se wã kata-gle kepi
When preparing it, we add other things;
Je ra jebi í õr-gẽ-ra jirö kuẽ-gẽ inga
we look for other ingredients and eat it.
jirö í (m) duá yule-gẽ kwãwã Je wa yeke-gẽ
It does not require much effort.’
je (_) ka rö kenẽ' tã'ĩ kuna (m)
